Locked architectural decisions

Based on the architecture you've locked:

businessTransactionId is the only mandatory metadata field.
It is the canonical identifier for the Business Transaction and the idempotency key.
All other fields are optional metadata supplied by the calling application.
Parmana treats metadata as immutable once the Business Transaction is created.
Policy evaluation operates only on the signals object. Metadata identifies and provides context for the transaction but is not evaluated by policy logic.

{
  "$schema": "https://json-schema.org/draft/2020-12/schema",
  "$id": "https://schemas.parmana.ai/common/metadata.schema.json",
  "title": "Metadata",
  "description": "Canonical Business Transaction metadata.",
  "type": "object",
  "additionalProperties": false,
  "required": [
    "businessTransactionId"
  ],
  "properties": {
    "businessTransactionId": {
      "type": "string",
      "description": "Unique Business Transaction identifier.",
      "minLength": 1,
      "maxLength": 255
    },
    "correlationId": {
      "type": "string",
      "description": "Optional correlation identifier used by the calling application."
    },
    "tenantId": {
      "type": "string",
      "description": "Optional tenant identifier for multi-tenant deployments."
    },
    "sourceSystem": {
      "type": "string",
      "description": "Originating application or service."
    },
    "submittedBy": {
      "type": "string",
      "description": "Identity of the calling application or principal."
    },
    "submittedAt": {
      "type": "string",
      "format": "date-time",
      "description": "UTC timestamp when the Business Transaction was submitted."
    }
  },
  "examples": [
    {
      "businessTransactionId": "PAY-1001",
      "correlationId": "CORR-20260626-001",
      "tenantId": "tenant-001",
      "sourceSystem": "payment-service",
      "submittedBy": "payment-api",
      "submittedAt": "2026-06-26T10:15:40Z"
    }
  ]
}